# Full Wallet Addresses — No Truncation

**Never truncate wallet or contract addresses.** Always show the complete address.

## Bad

```
0xac3e...ffc7
0x8f73...e5d8c
```

## Good

```
0xac3e216bd55860912062a4027a03b99587b7ffc7
0x8f73b65b4caaf64fba2af91cc5d4a2a1318e5d8c
```

## Why

Truncated addresses are useless — the user has to ask you to look it up every time they want to check a wallet on DeBank, BscScan, or any other tool. A full address is immediately copy-pasteable.

## Where this applies

- Research markdown files (`research/*.md`)
- Canvas files (`*.canvas.tsx`)
- Dune query labels
- Chat messages referencing wallets
- Any output that includes a blockchain address
